{"title_page": "Pavel \u0158ezn\u00ed\u010dek", "text_new": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]] -->\n | name = Pavel \u0158ezn\u00ed\u010dek\t \n | image =\t  \n | birth_date = {{birth date|1942|1|30|df=y}}\n | birth_place = [[Blansko]], [[Czechoslovakia]]<br>(now [[Czech Republic]]) \n | death_date= {{death date and age|2018|9|19|1942|1|30|df=y}}\n | death_place= [[Prague]], Czech Republic\n | occupation = Writer, poet, translator\n | genre = \n | influences = \n | influenced = \n | notes =\n}}\n\n'''Pavel \u0158ezn\u00ed\u010dek''' (30 January 1942 \u2013 19 September 2018) was a [[Czech people|Czech]] [[writer]] and surrealist poet. In addition to his writing career he also translated from French ([[Joyce Mansour]], [[Ambroise Vollard]], [[Benjamin P\u00e9ret]] and others). He finished a secondary school in 1959. Since 1965 he worked in many manual professions. Since 1970's, he lived in [[Prague]]; and since 2002, he was a [[retirement|pensioner]].\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\nMany of his books were first published outside of (then) [[Czechoslovakia]], before coming into print in his home country.\n\n'''Poetry'''\n\n* ''Blbec'', 1986 (''L'Imb\u00e9cile'')\n* ''Kr\u00e1ter Resnik a jin\u00e9 b\u00e1sn\u011b'', 1990\n* ''Tab\u00e1kov\u00e9 vejce'', 1991\n* ''Plovac\u00ed sval'', 1995\n* ''Hrozba v\u00fdtahu'', 2001\n* ''Atent\u00e1t ve van\u011b'', 2002\n* ''Kakod\u00e9monick\u00fd kart\u00e1\u010d'', 2006\n\n'''Prose'''\n\n* ''Strop'', outside Czechoslovakia 1983, in Czechoslovakia 1991\n* ''Vedro'', 1993\n* ''Zv\u00ed\u0159ata'', 1993\n* ''[[Alexandr v tramvaji]]'', 1994\n* ''Zrcadlov\u00fd pes'', 1994\n* ''Cerf volant'', 1995\n* ''Holi\u010d a boty'', 1997\n* ''Natrhne\u0161 nehtem hlavy jejich'', 2003\n\n'''Works dedicated to the [[Brno]] [[Counterculture|underground]]'''\n\n* ''Hv\u011bzdy kvelbu'', 1992\n* ''Popel \u017ehne'', 1996\n* ''Bl\u00e1zny \u0161at\u00ed stvol'', 1998\n\n'''Works in English''' \n* [http://cafeirreal.alicewhittenburg.com/reznicek.htm \"Watches\" (story)] in ''[[The Cafe Irreal]]''\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.czlit.cz/main.php?pageid=36&author_id=157 Profile in Czech]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reznicek, Pavel}}\n\n[[Category:Czech poets]]\n[[Category:Male poets]]\n[[Category:Czech male writers]]\n[[Category:Czech surrealist writers]]\n[[Category:Czech translators]]\n[[Category:French\u2013Czech translators]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]] -->\n | name = Pavel \u0158ezn\u00ed\u010dek   \t \n | image =\t  \n | birth_date = {{birth date|1942|1|30|df=y}}\n | birth_place = [[Blansko]], [[Czechoslovakia]]<br>(now [[Czech Republic]]) \n | death_date= {{death date and age|2018|9|19|1942|1|30|df=y}}\n | death_place= [[Prague]], Czech Republic\n | occupation = Writer, poet, translator\n | genre = \n | influences = \n | influenced = \n | notes =\n}}\n\n'''Pavel \u0158ezn\u00ed\u010dek''' (30 January 1942 \u2013 19 September 2018) was a [[Czech people|Czech]] [[writer]] and surrealist poet. In addition to his writing career he also translated from French ([[Joyce Mansour]], [[Ambroise Vollard]], [[Benjamin P\u00e9ret]] and others). He finished a secondary school in 1959. Since 1965 he worked in many manual professions. Since 1970's, he lived in [[Prague]]; and since 2002, he was a [[retirement|pensioner]].\n\n== Bibliography ==\n\nMany of his books were first published outside of (then) [[Czechoslovakia]], before coming into print in his home country.\n\n'''Poetry'''\n\n* ''Blbec'', 1986 (''L'Imb\u00e9cile'')\n* ''Kr\u00e1ter Resnik a jin\u00e9 b\u00e1sn\u011b'', 1990\n* ''Tab\u00e1kov\u00e9 vejce'', 1991\n* ''Plovac\u00ed sval'', 1995\n* ''Hrozba v\u00fdtahu'', 2001\n* ''Atent\u00e1t ve van\u011b'', 2002\n* ''Kakod\u00e9monick\u00fd kart\u00e1\u010d'', 2006\n\n'''Prose'''\n\n* ''Strop'', outside Czechoslovakia 1983, in Czechoslovakia 1991\n* ''Vedro'', 1993\n* ''Zv\u00ed\u0159ata'', 1993\n* ''[[Alexandr v tramvaji]]'', 1994\n* ''Zrcadlov\u00fd pes'', 1994\n* ''Cerf volant'', 1995\n* ''Holi\u010d a boty'', 1997\n* ''Natrhne\u0161 nehtem hlavy jejich'', 2003\n\n'''Works dedicated to the [[Brno]] [[Counterculture|underground]]'''\n\n* ''Hv\u011bzdy kvelbu'', 1992\n* ''Popel \u017ehne'', 1996\n* ''Bl\u00e1zny \u0161at\u00ed stvol'', 1998\n\n'''Works in English''' \n* [http://cafeirreal.alicewhittenburg.com/reznicek.htm \"Watches\" (story)] in ''[[The Cafe Irreal]]''\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.czlit.cz/main.php?pageid=36&author_id=157 Profile in Czech]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Reznicek, Pavel}}\n\n[[Category:Czech poets]]\n[[Category:Male poets]]\n[[Category:Czech male writers]]\n[[Category:Czech surrealist writers]]\n[[Category:Translators from French]]\n[[Category:Czech translators]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:2018 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "Jirka23", "label": "safe", "comment": "recat toCategory:French\u2013Czech translators", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pavel_%C5%98ezn%C3%AD%C4%8Dek"}
{"title_page": "Great Escape (South Korean TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Korean television program}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Great Escape [[File:Republic Of Korea Broadcasting-TV Rating System(15).svg|24px|Republic_Of_Korea_Broadcasting-TV_Rating_System(15).svg]]\n| image                    = Great Escape (South Korea TV series) poster.jpg\n| image_size               = 350px\n| caption                  = Promotional Poster of Season 1\n| show_name_2              = Big Escape\n| native_name              = {{Infobox name module|hangul=\ub300\ud0c8\ucd9c}}\n| genre                    = [[Reality television]], [[Escape the room|Room Escape]]\n| creator                  = [[Jung Jong-yeon]]\n| writer                   = Kim Jung-sun, Park Seon-yu, Jung Da-hee, Heo Jung-hee\n| director                 = Yi Chan-hyun, Choi Yoon-hee, Kim Sae-hee, Ha Moo-sung\n| starring                 = [[#Cast|Various artists]]\n| country                  = [[South Korea]]\n| language                 = [[Korean language|Korean]]\n| num_seasons              = 3\n| num_episodes             = {{plainlist|\n*'''Season 1:''' 13\n*'''Season 2:''' 13\n*'''Season 3:''' 6 (as of {{date|4/5/2020}})}}\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| producer                 = Rhee Myoung-Han, Kim Sock-hyun, Kim Joon-hoon\n| location                 = South Korea\n| cinematography           = Shin Sung-hwan\n| camera                   = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multi-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 60\u201390 minutes\n| company                  = [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN]]\n| channel                  = tvN\n| picture_format           = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| first_aired              = {{plainlist|\n*'''Season 1:''' {{start and end date|df=y|2018|7|1|2018|9|23}}\n*'''Season 2:''' {{start and end date|df=y|2019|3|17|2019|6|9}}\n*'''Season 3:''' {{start date|df=y|2020|3|1}} \u2013 present}}\n| website                  = http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape3\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n|title = [[Korean name]]\n|hangul = {{linktext|\ub300|\ud0c8\ucd9c}}\n|hanja  = \u5927\u9003\u51fa\n|rr = daetalchul\n|mr = \n|color = lavender\n}}\n'''''Great Escape''''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub300\ud0c8\ucd9c||daetalchul}}) is a South Korean [[Television comedy|television entertainment program]] featuring Kang Ho-dong, Kim Jong-min, Shindong, Yoo Byung-jae, Kim Dong-hyun and P.O.\n\nSeason 1 was televised on [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN]] Sundays at 10:40 pm ([[Time in South Korea|KST]]) starting 1 July and ended on 23 September 2018.\n\nSeason 2 was broadcast between 17 March and 9 June 2019.<ref>{{citeweb|title=\u2018\ub300\ud0c8\ucd9c\u2019 \uc624\ub298(23\uc77c) \ube44\ud558\uc778\ub4dc \uc2a4\ud1a0\ub9ac \ub300\ubc29\ucd9c\u2026\ucd08\ub300\ud615 \ubc00\uc2e4 \ud0c4\uc0dd\uae30|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1573496|lang=ko|date=23 September 2018|accessdate=23 September 2018|website=tenasia|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180923085534/http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1573496|archivedate=23 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Season2>{{citeweb|url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3553443|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] '\ub300\ud0c8\ucd9c2', \uc624\ub294 3\uc6d417\uc77c \uccab\ubc29\u2026 \uc6d0\ub144 \uba64\ubc84 \uadf8\ub300\ub85c|date=21 February 2019|website=\ub274\uc2a41|lang=ko|access-date=21 February 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090811/http://news1.kr/articles/?3553443|archivedate=27 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSeason 3 started broadcast on 1 March 2020 at 10:40 pm.<ref name=season3>{{citeweb|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/275478|title=\u2018\ub300\ud0c8\ucd9c3\u2019 \uba64\ubc84 \ubcc0\ub3d9 \uc5c6\uc774 3\uc6d4 1\uc77c\uc5d0 \ub2e4\uc2dc \ub3cc\uc544\uc628\ub2e4!|lang=ko|date=30 January 2020|accessdate=6 February 2020|website=iMBC|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206105727/http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/275478|archivedate=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\n\nBefore each phase of the escape challenge, the members first gather in the bus. Since the second challenge (third episode) of Season 1, the program team will assign the captain '''(\uc8fc\uc7a5)''' of the period in response to the performance of the members of the previous challenge, and the captain will receive an armband. Prior to arriving at the location, members will wear eye masks, and the staff will lead the members to the start point in the large secret room. After fulfilling the instructions of the staff, the members can remove the eye mask. In each challenge, members need to use the clues in the room to gradually explore the large secret room until all members escape from the location.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape/3/Contents/Html|title=Introduction to Great Escape (Season 1)|website=tvN|lang=ko|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719084306/http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape/3/Contents/Html|archivedate=19 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nEach challenge has a different theme, and members will learn about the context of the background story from the clues during the exploration. In addition to finding and cracking the clues, members may need to interact with the story characters played by the staff (such as helping the character, leading the character to escape, etc.) before they can escape from the large secret room. There is no stipulated time limit for each escape challenge, it will only end when all members and story characters (if any) have successfully escaped.\n\nFor Season 2, a major change being added to the show is that there is a possibility of failure to escape. The recording of the challenge ends once it happens. Another added change is that there is a possibility that cast member(s) would get eliminated in the midst of escaping, based on situations (e.g. \"dead\" or \"missing\" during the attempt) and the decisions of the production team. The eliminated cast member(s) will get off from work.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape2/7/Contents/Html|title=Introduction to Great Escape (Season 2)|website=tvN|lang=ko|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719084414/http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape2/7/Contents/Html|archivedate=19 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> There is no longer any assignment of the captain '''(\uc8fc\uc7a5)'''.\n\n==Slogan==\nThe slogan of the show is '''\"\ub098\uac00\uc57c\uc0b0\ub2e4\"''' (Escape and Survive) as shown in the promotional poster for Season 1.\n\n==Airtime==\n{|class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|-\n!Season!!Airdate!!Broadcast Start Time\n|-\n|1||1 July \u2013 23 September 2018||rowspan=3|Sundays 10:40 pm (KST)\n|-\n|2||17 March \u2013 9 June 2019\n|-\n|3||1 March 2020 \u2013 present\n|-\n|}\n{{-}}\n==Cast==\n===Season 1===\n{{hidden begin\n|title=List of Cast (Season 1)\n|titlestyle=background:lightGray\n}}\n{|class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|-\n! Name!! Episode!! Role & Character!! Notes\n|-\n|[[Kang Ho-dong]]||rowspan=6|1 \u2013 13\n|style=text-align:left|Leading the team with the strongest teamwork and challenging to escape with a battle-like temperament!\n|rowspan=6|<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape/4/Contents/Html|title=Great Escape Cast Member Introduction (Season 1)|website=tvN|accessdate=5 August 2018|lang=ko|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190719084513/http://program.tving.com/tvn/greatescape/4/Contents/Html|archivedate=19 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kim Jong-min]] ([[Koyote]])\n|style=text-align:left|Hidden behind the character 'Eri'! He aim to be the 'Ace' with unpredictable reasoning that made everyone surprised!\n|-\n|[[Shindong]] ([[Super Junior]])\n|style=text-align:left|The birth of a new mystery prodigy?! A veteran idol with the sharpness of finding evidences as being demonstrated by this incredible being!\n|-\n|[[