ent to Great Britain, but in March 1946 decided to return to his native country. There, he took command of 7th Air Bomb Regiment in [[\u0141\u0119czyca]] and in August 1947 he became commander of the famous [[Polish Air Force]] Academy in [[D\u0119blin]].\n\nHe was arrested on August 9, 1951 and wrongly accused of being a British spy. \u015acibior was tortured for many months, then sentenced to death. He was charged with for his service in the [[Polish Air Forces in France and Great Britain|Polish Air Forces]] (Polskie Si\u0142y Powietrzne) fighting alongside the allies. His execution took place on August 7, 1952 in the infamous Communist [[Mokot\u00f3w Prison]] in [[Warsaw]].\n\nIn 1956 &ndash; following political changes in Poland &ndash; \u015acibior was officially \"rehabilitated\" posthumously. His symbolic tomb is located at Warsaw's [[Pow\u0105zki Cemetery]].\n\n==Sources==\n\n* {{in lang|en}} http://home.clara.net/clinchy/neeb5.htm (English),\n* {{in lang|pl}} http://www.polishairforce.pl/news2004.html (Polish)\n* {{in lang|pl}} http://www.eduskrypt.pl/55_rocznica_wydania_wyrokow_smierci_na_lotnikow-info-5954.html (Polish)\n* {{in lang|en}} https://web.archive.org/web/20090805130743/http://www.cmentarzekomunalne.com.pl/cmentarze/wojskzasl.html (tomb)\n* {{in lang|pl}} https://web.archive.org/web/20080804123729/http://www.polskaludowa.com/wydarzenia/Fieldorf3.htm\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scibior, Szczepan}}\n[[Category:1903 births]]\n[[Category:1952 deaths]]\n[[Category:Burials at Pow\u0105zki Cemetery]]\n[[Category:Polish People's Republic rehabilitations]]\n[[Category:Executed people from \u0141\u00f3d\u017a Voivodeship]]\n[[Category:People executed by the Polish People's Republic]]\n[[Category:Executed military personnel]]\n[[Category:People from Podd\u0119bice County]]\n[[Category:Polish World War II pilots]]\n[[Category:Bomber pilots]]\n[[Category:Shot-down aviators]]\n[[Category:Polish prisoners of war]]\n[[Category:World War II prisoners of war held by Germany